article.description: St. Francis, Pa. 63, St. Francis, NY 50
article.headline: St. Francis, Pa. 63, St. Francis, NY 50
article.linkText: St. Francis, Pa. 63, St. Francis, NY 50
article.story: NEW YORK (AP) -- Bassirou Dieng scored 20 points to help St. Francis of Pennsylvania snap a three-game losing streak with a 63-50 victory over St. Francis of New York on Thursday night. Chris Berry added 10 points for the Red Flash (6-18, 4-9 Northeast Conference). Ricky Cadell had 15 points for the Terriers (5-20, 2-12) in their eighth straight loss. The Terriers' Bass Yessoufou scored the first three points of the second half to cut the deficit to 30-25. The Red Flash then responded with a 20-8 burst that turned the game into a rout at 58-33. Dieng had seven points in the run.
